    {
      "id": "8183d1d3_de3fde3e",
      "file_path": "runtime-acm/src/main/resources/openapi/openapi.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "It would be great to refer to the Java classes that are returned/sent\n\n        200:\n          description: Serialised instance of<br>https://github.com/onap/policy-models/blob/master/models-tosca/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/tosca/authorative/concepts/ToscaServiceTemplate.java",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2022-11-02 17:55:07.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "bf1e3bbc_f3d92412",
      "file_path": "runtime-acm/src/main/resources/openapi/openapi.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 72,
      "message": "Lines 70-75:\n\nI know you have put a lot of effort into defining the schemas below but they are not in the format that we actually get back. I think it would be better to just refer to the Java type definitions and to put in examples.\n\nFor example, replace lines 70-75 with:\n          content:\n            application/json:\n              schema:\n                title: ToscaServiceTemplate\n                type: object\n              example:\n                $ref: \"examples/GetAllACDefinitions.json\"\n            application/yaml:\n              schema:\n                title: ToscaServiceTemplate\n                type: object\n              example:\n                $ref: \"examples/GetAllACDefinitions.yaml\"\n\n\nAnd the we put examples of the output in the examples/<blah blah>.<json|yaml> files.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2022-11-02 18:07:56.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "4152eb67_4abe8d57",
      "file_path": "runtime-acm/src/main/resources/openapi/openapi.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 68,
      "message": "This works nicely, and it puts a hyperlink to the real Java class there for users:\n        200:\n          description: Serialised instance of\n            <a href=\"https://github.com/onap/policy-models/blob/master/models-tosca/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/models/tosca/authorative/concepts/ToscaServiceTemplate.java\">ToscaServiceTemplate</a>",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2787,
        "name": "Liam Fallon",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "liam.fallon@est.tech",
        "username": "liamfallon"
      },
      "updated": "2022-11-03 10:00:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "8183d1d3_de3fde3e",
      "unresolved": true
    },
